<section xml:id="section-similarity-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p>
We'll repeat the definition of <term>similar matrices</term> here so that we can attach some notation to the notion,
and then we'll add a definition related to
<xref ref="activity-similarity-equiv-rel" />.
</p>

<p><dl>

	<li>
	<title>similar matrices</title>
	<idx><h>similar matrices</h></idx>
	<idx><h>matrix</h><h>similarity</h></idx>
	<p> a pair of square matrices <m>A</m> and <m>B</m> for which there exists an invertible matrix <m>P</m> satisfying <m>B=\inv{P}AP</m>; we will write <m>B \similar A</m> to indicate this relationship </p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>similarity class</title>
	<idx><h>similarity class</h></idx>
	<p>the subset of <m>\matrixring_n(\C)</m> consisting of all matrices that are similar to a particular matrix</p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
